# Lovely Home: Aesthetic & Feature Analysis

Based on the [current Lovely Home site](https://lovelyhome.com.co/) and our premium benchmark, [Outsite](https://outsite.co/), here is a breakdown of the key features and aesthetic requirements for the new Lovely Home platform.

## 1. Aesthetic Direction: Premium & Dynamic

We need to transition Lovely Home from a standard functional template to a high-end, dynamic experience that rivals Outsite.

*   **Color Palette:** We need to move away from generic colors. Outsite uses a stark, high-contrast palette (very dark off-black backgrounds with off-white text and structural borders) mixed with gorgeous, large-format photography. Lovely Home needs a curated, harmonious palette (e.g., elegant dark mode with sleek accents, or a very clean, airy light mode with glassmorphism).
*   **Typography:** Outsite uses modern, legible sans-serif fonts with tight tracking for headers and readable body text. We must use a premium Google Font (like Inter, Outfit, or Plus Jakarta Sans) instead of browser defaults.
*   **Imagery:** This is crucial. Outsite relies on huge, immersive, edge-to-edge photography of their locations and people. We must ensure property images are the hero elements of the UI, not small thumbnails.
*   **Micro-interactions & Animations:** The site must feel alive. Hover states on property cards, smooth page transitions, and subtle reveal animations as the user scrolls will elevate the experience from simple to premium.

## 2. Core Functional Requirements

Based on what both sites offer, the front-end UI needs to support these core features:

### A. The Booking Engine (User Facing)
*   **Search & Filter:** Users need an intuitive way to search by dates, guests, and location (Medellín/El Poblado).
*   **Property Cards:** High-quality cards displaying the hero image, title, location, key amenities (cleaning, workspace, internet), and price.
*   **Property Details Page:** Immersive hero image gallery, detailed description, list of amenities, location map, and a clear booking widget (supporting COP, USD, EUR).
*   **User Accounts ("Mi Cuenta"):** A portal for guests to view reservations and manage profiles.

### B. Business & Community Focus
*   **Community / Social Proof:** Outsite heavily emphasizes community ("Meet the people who made the world their office"). Lovely Home currently has a "What Our Guests Say" section. We need a beautifully designed testimonial or social proof section.
*   **Long-Term vs. Short-Term:** The UI must clearly differentiate or seamlessly cater to both short stays and long-term ("Alquiler a largo plazo") rentals.
*   **Destinations/Neighborhoods:** A dedicated section highlighting the vibe of Medellín, Provenza, and El Poblado.

## 3. Next Steps for UI Generation

When you use the AI UI generators (like Google Stitch or v0), use these prompts based on our analysis:

> "Create a premium, modern property listing card for a short-term rental platform. Use a sleek dark mode aesthetic with high-contrast text. Include a large, edge-to-edge hero image, property title, top 3 amenities (fast wifi, workspace, cleaning), and a price per night. Include subtle glassy hover effects."

> "Design a hero section for a premium Coliving and short-term rental website. The design should feature a massive, high-quality background video or image of a modern apartment. The headline should be bold and modern, with a clear 'Explore Locations' call to action. Use modern typography like typography like 'Inter'."
